




TY  - JOUR
T1  - Parallel Line Assignment Problems
AU  - Klein, Morton
AU  - Takamori, Hiroshi
Y1  - 1972/09/01
PY  - 1972
DA  - 1972/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.19.1.1
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.19.1.1
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1
EP  - 10
VL  - 19
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Two problems involving the assignment of men to jobs, in a production system with parallel lines, to maximize the steady state system production rate are studied. In the first, in which a man's production rate is independent of the line to which he is assigned, a simple rule ?group the fastest men in the same line? is shown to be optimal. In the second, in which production rates are dependent on the production line, an algorithm is developed to obtain a solution.
AB  - Two problems involving the assignment of men to jobs, in a production system with parallel lines, to maximize the steady state system production rate are studied. In the first, in which a man's production rate is independent of the line to which he is assigned, a simple rule ?group the fastest men in the same line? is shown to be optimal. In the second, in which production rates are dependent on the production line, an algorithm is developed to obtain a solution.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.19.1.1
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.19.1.1
Y2  - 2024/03/27
